						 <p>Oil (n.) The remains of ancient bacteria, conveniently liquefied and converted to pure combustible hydrocarbons.</p> <p>Oil is of course the basis for modern <a href="http://wiki.hintjens.com/wiki:civilisation">civilisation</a>, and we finish it off, we might do well to reflect on the fate of many past civilizations that ran out of essential raw materials and then collapsed.</p> <p>KÃ¼bler-Ross wrote that the five stages of acceptance of a terminal disease are denial, anger, bargaining, depression, and acceptance. Most of the western world still lives in denial, and will probably slip directly to depression. I don't have anything against a major collapse of civilization. I just don't want to be there when it happens.</p> <p>by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pieterh" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=99&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1485775378" alt="pieterh" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=99)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pieterh" >pieterh</a></span></p> 
